GxClientModels

Class GxClientAddRangeSelectionModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • GxClientModels.GxClientAddRangeSelectionModel

  • public class GxClientAddRangeSelectionModel
extends java.lang.Object
    The model is used to compose a range selection model in order to be applied on the client. Ranges are normally bounded by a start and end row. However it is also possible to define a range unbounded by rows (ie to contain all rows). For an unbounded range, do not provided start or end row positions.
